msContents.summary: Versified treatise on common Arabic grammar and Arabic and Persian vocabulary in 30 poems. Titles are in Arabic; verses are in Ottoman Turkish with the vocabulary words in Persian and Arabic.

textLang.#text: Chiefly Ottoman Turkish with Persian and Arabic vocabulary and headings in Arabic

supportDesc.extent: 58 leaves : 197 x 155 (134 x 92) mm, bound to 197 x 160 x 8 mm

layoutDesc.layout: 13 lines in two hemistichs either in two columns or offset.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Naskh in black ink; pointed, vocalized.

decoNote: Rubrications in red. Headpiece in gold and red (f. 2v); first page opening text border-ruled in gold and black (f. 2v-3r).

binding.p: Quarter covers with flap in green paper over pasteboard, brown leather spine and fore-edge hinge.

provenance: Formerly owned by Qusṭanṭīn ibn Lūdūlf (f. 1v, f. 57v).
Another owner's seal (f. 1r). Unidentified sale (Latin/French catalog clipping).
